  "abstract": "Atomic, review-first best practices for Trino SQL, plan analysis, connector-aware tuning, and Hive/Iceberg troubleshooting. The package teaches agents to read plans first, preserve pushdown and pruning, reason about dynamic filtering and join distribution, and separate engine behavior from connector-specific behavior. For Lakehouse, it adds connector-boundary guidance and routes full advice only when the underlying table type is Hive or Iceberg.",
